parts and meteors are now falling to Earth!

01:28:24.220 --> 01:28:28.440
- Uh, I don't believe anyone could have predicted this.
- Either way, we have quite the mystical view here.

01:28:28.460 --> 01:28:31.930
So, what does the comet's
nucleus splitting mean for us?

01:28:31.950 --> 01:28:37.760
The comet's not within the Roche limit, so the nucleus
itself must've had a structural weakness for this to happen.

01:28:37.780 --> 01:28:42.610
Comet Shoemaker-Levy 9 broke apart
and collided with Jupiter in 1994.

01:28:43.150 --> 01:28:45.290
- There were at least 21 fragments...
- I'm going outside to take a look.

01:28:45.310 --> 01:28:48.720
- The fragments will likely burn up well before reaching the ground.
- Does it pose a danger?

01:28:48.740 --> 01:28:53.090
Probability of a meteor actually landing
on a populated area is quite small.

01:28:53.110 --> 01:28:54.720
Never foresaw this development.

01:28:54.740 --> 01:28:58.840
- To predict the trajectory...
- As we stand here witnessing this spectacle,

01:28:58.860 --> 01:29:00.340
unassisted...

01:29:00.360 --> 01:29:01.660
and with our bare eyes,

01:29:01.680 --> 01:29:07.060
it strikes me that living in such an age
has never felt more fortunate than now.

01:29:09.670 --> 01:29:10.790
Hey...

01:29:11.300 --> 01:29:12.380
Who...

01:29:12.400 --> 01:29:14.090
are you?

01:29:16.920 --> 01:29:18.290
Who?

01:29:18.650 --> 01:29:20.330
Who?

01:29:20.420 --> 01:29:22.330
Who is he?

01:29:22.350 --> 01:29:24.100
Someone precious.

01:29:24.120 --> 01:29:26.090
Someone I shouldn't forget!

01:29:26.110 --> 01:29:28.810
Someone I didn't want to!

01:29:28.830 --> 01:29:30.500
Who?

01:29:30.520 --> 01:29:31.580
Who?!

01:29:31.600 --> 01:29:33.480
Who are you?!

01:29:33.500 --> 01:29:36.240
What's your name?!

01:29:41.100 --> 01:29:42.550
Oh no!

01:29:42.610 --> 01:29:43.970
Ah! Argh!

01:29:47.750 --> 01:29:48.870
Ungh!

01:30:01.930 --> 01:30:04.490
